To install docker into your ubuntu virtual machine you can simply type
sudo snap install docker
sudo snap services
NOTE: If you are using ubuntu ensure thatg you write all commands with sudo(Super user do) else it will deny the permission.

docker version
//this commanad is used to check the version of your docker if properly installed

docker run hello-world
//if you want to know whether you have completely installed docker on your machine type this command this will give you the confirmation like this
===================================================================================================================================================
Hello from Docker!
This message shows that your installation appears to be working correctly.

This hello-world is nothing but an image
